        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-04-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-04-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="559"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d559">
                <head>Municipal Council of Preston</head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Preston</placeName>, <date
                        ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content" calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1865-04-27">April 27, 1865</date>
                </dateline>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="italic">Resolution passed in the borough of Preston, in the county of
                        Lancaster</hi>.</p>
                <p>At a meeting of the council of the said borough, held on the 27th day of April,
                    1865, present the right worshipful Joseph Isherwood, mayor, in the chair, it
                    was</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Unanimously resolved</hi>, That this council desire to express
                    their utter abhorrence of the assassination of the President of the United
                    States of America, and to condole and sympathize with the American nation upon
                    the loss they have sustained through the sudden and lamented death of their
                    President.</p>
                <p>Given under the common seal of the said borough, the day and year above
                    mentioned.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>JOSEPH ISHERWOOD, </signed>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mayor</hi>, [<hi rend="smallcaps">l. s.</hi>] <lb/>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Ascroft</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Town
                    Clerk</hi>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
